<kml>

<concept name=Military-Task>
<superconcept name=Action>

<definition>

   the tasks that <conceptref name=Military-Unit>s can perform to achieve
   offensive, defensive, and security objectives
  
</definition>

<comment>
These military tasks are defined in 
<a href=http://www.adtdl.army.mil/cgi-bin/atdl.dll/fm/3-90/pref.htm>FM 3-90</a>
</comment>

<p>
<p>

ACTIONS BY FRIENDLY FORCES

<neighborlist>

  <neighbor name=Attack-by-Fire>
     Attack-by-Fire uses direct fires, supported by indirect fires,
     to engage an enemy without closing with him to destroy, suppress,
     fix, or deceive him
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Bypass>
     Bypass is a military action by friendly forces in which a unit
     maneuvers around an obstacle
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Clear>
    Clear is a tactical mission task to remove enemy forces within an
    assigned area
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Follow-and-Assume>
     Follow-and-Assume is a tactical mission task to follow a force
     conducting an offensive operation and to continue the mission if the
     lead force is disabled
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Follow-and-Support>
     Follow-and-Support is a tactical mission task to follow and
     support a lead force conducting an offensive operation
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Occupy>
     Occupy is a tactical mission task to move a friendly force into
     an area and to control it
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Reconstitute-Unit>
     Reconstitute-Unit is a tactical mission task in which a military unit
     restores the full <slot>combat-strength</slot> of another unit
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Retain>
     Retain is a tactical mission task to ensure a terrain remains
     free of enemy occupation or use
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Seize>
     Seize is a tactical mission task to take possession of a designated
     area
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Support-by-Fire>
     Support-by-Fire is a tactical mission task in which a maneuver
     force moves to a position where it can engage the enemy by direct
     fire in support of another maneuvering force
  </neighbor>

</neighborlist>

<p>

EFFECTS ON ENEMY FORCES

<neighborlist>

  <neighbor name=Annihilate-Unit>
     Annihilate-Unit is a tactical mission task in which one military unit
     annihilates another     
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Block-Avenue-of-Approach>
     Block-Avenue-of-Approach is a tactical mission task that prevents
     an enemy's advance along an avenue of approach
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Canalize>
     Canalize is a tactical mission task in which a military unit
     restricts enemy movement to a narrow zone
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Contain>
     Contain is a tactical mission task in which a military unit
     stops, holds, or surrounds enemy forces
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Defeat-Unit>
     Defeat-Unit is a tactical mission task in which one military unit
     defeats another (i.e. reduces its <slot>combat-strength</slot>
     to defeated)
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Destroy-Unit>
     Destroy-Unit is a tactical mission task in which one military unit
     destroys the <slot>combat-strength</slot> of another military
     unit
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Disrupt>
     Disrupt is a tactical mission task to upset an enemy action
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Fix>
     Fix is a tactical mission task to prevent the enemy from moving
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Interdict>
     Interdict is a tactical mission task to prevent, disrupt, or
     delay the enemy's use of an area or route
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Neutralize-Unit>
     Neutralize-Unit is a tactical mission task in which one military unit
     neutralizes the <slot>combat-strength</slot> of another military
     unit
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Suppress>
     Suppress is a tactical mission task to degrade the performance of
     a force or weapon system temporarily
  </neighbor>

</neighborlist>

<p>
SECURITY OPERATIONS

<neighborlist>

  <neighbor name=Guard>
    Guard is also a security action.  Guard means to fix an enemy
    ground force before it can engage the main body.
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Screen>
    Screen is also a security action.  Screen primarily provides early
    warning to a protected force.
  </neighbor>

</neighborlist>


</kml>

